Name: ovarian carcinoma
Definition: An ovarian cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue and is located_in the ovary.

Name: malignant ovarian Brenner tumor
Definition: A malignant ovarian surface epithelial-stromal neoplasm that has_material_basis_in the surface epithelium of the ovary.
Synonym: meningioma of the Posterior Cranial Fossa

Name: ovarian carcinosarcoma
Definition: A malignant ovarian surface epithelial-stromal neoplasm that is a mixed cell type cancer that has_material_basis_in carcinomatous (epithelial tissue) and sarcomatous (connective tissue) components.
